All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AdjacencyListGraph<V>
An implementation of the Graph interface that uses an adjacency list to represent the graph.
AdjacencyMatrix<T>
AdjacencyMatrix implementation of the Graph interface.
Convergence
A class that provides a main method to demonstrate the convergence of the PageRank algorithm on a generated graph.
CycleCount
The CycleCount class contains methods to check if a given graph contains a cycle.
DataGenerator
A utility class for generating data and graph for PageRank algorithm.
ExperimentWithList
The Main class is the entry point of the PageRank experiment program.
ExperimentWithMatrix
A class for running an experiment with the PageRank algorithm using an adjacency matrix representation of a graph.
FileReader
A utility class to read data from a file.
Graph<T>
An interface that represents a graph data structure.
GraphTestDataGenerator
A utility class for generating random test data for graph algorithms.
MatrixComparission
A class for comparing the performance of PageRank algorithm using adjacency matrix and adjacency list implementations.
PageRank<T>
This class implements the PageRank algorithm on a graph.
PageRank
The PageRank class provides a main method to calculate the PageRank for multiple datasets.
PageRankResult<T>
A class that represents the result of the PageRank algorithm, including the PageRank scores, convergence history, and epsilon threshold used in the calculation.
